The bizarre statistics, given Kenya’s distance running talent, have led Athletics Kenya (AK) to working on a programme they hope will break the jinx at this year’s Tokyo Olympics that will run from July 23 to August 8. 

AK President Jack Tuwei says the federation will identify medal probables and put them in camp as part of the preparations for Tokyo. 

He said that the athletes who will be selected must undergo the mandatory tests a requirement by the Athletics Integrity Unit (AIU) as one way of avoiding the 2019 scenario where athletes who had been selected to compete in the 5,000m were dropped ahead of the World Championships in Doha, Qatar. 



