“We are working on a plan with Anti-Doping Agency in Kenya (Adak) where we want to identify athletes who will be able to compete in the Olympics Games because competition keeps changing and we cannot rely on those athletes who have always represented the country. 

“We shall select the probable and send them into the camp where they will start vigorous training ahead of the National Trials where the best will be selected. The athletes must undergo various testing by Adak which is a requirement by the AIU,” said Tuwei. 

Tuwei also noted that AK was focusing of warding off the middle distance challenge from Uganda and Ethiopia especially. 



